    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zulu necklaces made of any or all of wooden beads, seeds, bone, animal horn, teeth and claws. After being identified by the king as having distinguished himself in battle, a warrior was granted permission to create a necklace to be worn as a mark of valor. The necklace was a unique creation, with the design, carving of the beads and stringing of the necklace all done by the warrior himself.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
